article.headline: Queens defeats Fairleigh Dickinson 97-84

images.caption: Fairleigh Dickinson Knights vs. Queens NC Royals: Full Highlights

article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- — AJ McKee's 26 points helped Queens defeat Fairleigh Dickinson 97-84 on Wednesday night. McKee was 11 of 19 shooting, including 2 for 6 from 3-point range, and went 2 for 3 from the line for the Royals (3-3). Deyton Albury scored 21 points while going 6 of 11 and 8 of 10 from the free throw line, and added five assists. Logan Threatt was 5 of 8 shooting, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 2 for 4 from the line to finish with 14 points. Sean Moore finished with 21 points and 10 rebounds for the Knights (4-2). Ansley Almonor added 18 points, six rebounds and two blocks for Fairleigh Dickinson. Joe Munden Jr. also had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
